claim.claim-text:
An optical coupler device, especially for monitoring purposes in an optical point-to-point transmission link (1), comprising:
(a) a first (13a), a second (13b) and a third (13c) optical port;
(i) the optical coupler device (13) being configured to transmit a first optical signal (SDS) received at the first optical port (13a) to the second optical port (13b) and to transmit a second optical signal (SUS) received at the second optical (13b) port to the first (13a) and third (13c) optical port according to a monitoring split ratio with respect to the optical power of the second optical signal (SUS), the first (SDS) and second (SUS) optical signal having a wavelength (λ1, λ2) lying in a first optical band;
(ii) the optical coupler device (13) being further configured to transmit a third (Smon) and a fourth optical signal (Smon,r) received at the third (13c) and the second (13b) optical port to the respective other optical port, the third (Smon) and fourth (Smon,r) optical signal having a wavelength (λ3) lying in a second optical band;
characterized in
(b) that the optical coupler device (13) is configured to be controllable with respect to the monitoring split ratio and
(c) that the optical coupler device (13) further comprises a control means (19) adapted to receive a control signal and configured to control the optical coupler device (13) with respect to the monitoring split ratio in such a way that
(i) in a first work mode the second optical signal (SUS) is transmitted to the first optical port (13a), only, and
(ii) in a second work mode a major portion of the optical power of the second signal (SUS) is transmitted to the first optical port (13a) and a minor portion of the optical power of the second signal is (SUS) transmitted to the third optical port (13c).

An optical monitoring device for monitoring an optical point-to-point transmission link, characterized in that it comprises:
(a) an optical coupler device (13) according to one of the preceding claims, the first (13a) and second (13b) port of the optical coupler device (13) being connected to or defining a first and a second port of the monitoring device;
(b) an optical transmitter (17) adapted to create an optical monitoring signal (Smon) at a wavelength (λ3) lying in the second optical band of the optical coupler device (13);
(c) an optical receiver (21) capable of receiving signals (Smon,r; SUS) lying in the first and second optical bands; and
(d) a passive optical splitter/combiner (15) having a common port (15a) and a first (15b) and a second (15c) splitting port, the common port (15a) being connected to the third port (13c) of the optical coupler device (13), the first splitting port being (15b) connected to an optical output port of the optical transmitter (17) and the second splitting port (15c) being connected to an optical input port of the optical receiver (21),
(e) the passive optical splitter/combiner (15) being configured to transmit to the common port (15a) at least a portion of the optical power of the optical monitoring signal (Smon) created by the optical transmitter (17) and supplied to the first splitting port (15b) and to transmit to the second splitting port (15c) at least a portion of the optical power of an optical signal (Smon,r; SUS) supplied to the common port (15a).

An optical monitoring device for monitoring a plurality of optical point-to-point transmission links, characterized in that it comprises:
(a) a plurality of optical coupler devices (13) according to one of claims 1 to 5, each of which is configured to be connected to a first end, preferably a near end, and a second end, preferably a far end, of a dedicated optical point-to-point transmission link (1);
(b) an optical transmitter arrangement (370, 372) having a plurality of output ports and being adapted to create, at each output port, an optical monitoring signal (Smon), each of which has a wavelength lying in the second optical band of the optical coupler device;
(c) an optical receiver arrangement (380) having a plurality of input ports and being adapted to receive, at each input port, an optical signal having a wavelength lying in the first and second optical bands; and
(d) a plurality of passive optical splitter/combiners (15), each of which is dedicated to one of the optical coupler devices (13), each passive optical splitter/combiner (15) having a common port (15a) and a first (15b) and a second (15c) splitting port, the common port (15a) being connected to the third port (13c) of the dedicated optical coupler device (13), the first splitting port (15b) being connected to a dedicated optical output port of the optical transmitter arrangement (370, 372) and the second splitting port (15c) being connected to a dedicated optical input port of the optical receiver arrangement (380), each passive optical splitter/combiner(15) being configured to transmit to the common port at least a portion of the optical power of the optical signal created by the optical transmitter arrangement (370,372) and received at the first splitting port (15b) and to transmit to the second splitting port (15c) at least a portion of the optical power of the optical signal received at the common port (15a).

An optical coupler device, especially for monitoring purposes in an optical point-to-point transmission link (1), comprising:
(a) a first (13a), a second (13b) and a third (13c) optical port;
